Abiodun Nejo, Ado Ekiti The police in Ekiti State on Thursday arraigned a 44-year-old man, Tunji Aladewolu, before an Ado Ekiti Magistrate’s Court for allegedly stealing N100,000. The police prosecutor, Inspector Johnson Okunade, told the court that the defendant and others at large committed the offence around 6pm on November 6, 2020, at the Atikankan area of Ado Ekiti. He said, “The defendants did conspire with others to commit felony, to wit, stealing. The defendants thereby committed an offence contrary to and punishable under Section 516 of the Criminal Code Cap. C16 Vol. 1 Laws of Ekiti State of Nigeria 2012. “The defendant and others at large on the same date, time and place, did steal N100,000 belonging to one Iyanuoluwa Ayeni, thereby committing an offence contrary to Section 383 and punishable under Section 390 (9) of the Criminal Code C16 Vol.1 Laws of Ekiti State of Nigeria 2012.” Counsel for the defendant, Emmanual Folayan, urged the court to grant him bail, assuring that he would not jump bail. The Chief Magistrate, Mr Adedayo Oyebanji, granted the defendant bail in the sum of N50,000 with one surety in like sum. Oyebanji, who said the surety should produce evidence of landed property, adjourned the matter till February 15, 2021 Copyright PUNCH.
